      <h2 id='generalqs'>General</h2>

      <div class="qgroup">
        <div class="panel-group" id="Gaccordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">

          <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingGOne">
              <h3 class="panel-title">
                <a class="q" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseGOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseGOne">
                  What information do you collect from me?
                </a>
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseGOne" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingGOne">
              <div class="panel-body">
                <p class="answer">
                   From Facebook, we only get the information that is in your <b>public</b> Facebook profile -- that is, your name and your Facebook user ID, which allows us to save your trip history so that you can keep track of your green commutes. In terms of the data GreenBuggle generates, we save only the travel information that you select on our Trip Planner page (start and end destination, date, and estimated carbon emission). We do not, for instance, look at your email, friends list, or any other sensitive information.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingGTwo">
              <h3 class="panel-title">
                <a class="q" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseGTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseGTwo">
                  Do you guys calculate carbon footprints?
                </a>
              </h3>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseGTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingGTwo">
              <div class="panel-body">
                <p class="answer">
                  Not quite. Your carbon footprint encompasses a lot of things, including your water and electricity use, among other things. <b>GreenBuggle tries to help you calculate your everyday carbon emissions from various modes of transportation</b>, since fuel is a big part of most people's overall carbon footprint. From there, we hope you'll be able to make better and more informed decisions about your <b>travel options</b>, and then by extension, your carbon footprint.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingG3">
              <h3 class="panel-title">
                <a class="q" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseG3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseG3">
                  How accurate is GreenBuggle?
